html:

        <!-- must have position: relative on this, otherwise the google maps HTML elements which use position: absolute will be outside the viewport -->
        <div class="mlab_cp_googlemap_canvas mc_figure mc_interactive mc_map " style="pointer-events: none; position: relative; overflow: hidden; height: 300px" >
            Retrieving map ... 
        </div>

        <!-- must have position: relative on this, otherwise the google maps HTML elements which use position: absolute will be outside the viewport -->
        <div data-mlab-type="googlemap" style="display: block;" >
            <div class="mlab_cp_googlemap_canvas mc_figure mc_interactive mc_map" style="position: relative; overflow: hidden; height: 300px" >
                Retrieving map ... 
            </div>
        </div>

        tooltip: { nb_NO: Rediger kart, en_GB: Edit map, default: Edit map }

  # Configuration file for combatlog component
version: 1.1
developer: Arild Bergh @ Sinett/FFI.no
category: dataentry
name: combatlog
tooltip: Combat log updates
required_libs: {"runtime": ["socket.io.js"]}
credentials: ["url", "port"]
html: |
    <form id="form_newcombatlogitem" onsubmit="return false;">
        <label class="mc_text mc_display mc_medium" for="unit">Enhet:</label>
        <select class="mc_text mc_entry mc_input" id="cl_unit" name="unit" class="">
            <option>--Velg enhet--</option>
            <option value="Land">Land</option>
            <option value="Sj&oslash;">Sj&oslash;</option>
            <option value="Luft">Luft</option>
            <option value="OPS">OPS</option>
        </select>
        <label class="mc_text mc_display mc_medium" for="who">Hvem:</label>
            <input class="mc_text mc_entry mc_input" id="cl_who" type="text" name="who">
        <label class="mc_text mc_display mc_medium" for="where">Hvor:</label>
            <input class="mc_text mc_entry mc_input" id="cl_where" type="text" name="where">
        <label class="mc_text mc_display mc_medium" for="what">Hva:</label>
            <textarea class="mc_text mc_entry mc_input" id="cl_what" name="what" rows="3"></textarea>
        <!--div.clearfix-->
        <!--label(for='extra') Ekstra:--><!--textarea(name='extra', rows='3')-->
        <input type="hidden" name="owner_id" value="">
        <input type="hidden" name="session_id" value="">
       <button onclick="mlab.api.components.combatlog.sendCombatlogItem(); return false;">Save</button>
    </form>
